data.text:
MULBERRY -- Mrs. Josephine Edwards of Mulberry died of cancer Saturday (Oct. 25, 2003) at her home. She was 63.

Born Sept. 9, 1940, in Winter Haven, she was a lifelong resident of Polk County. She was a homemaker.

Mrs. Edwards is survived by her husband, Joseph Edwards Sr.; sons, Milton Edwards, Mark Edwards, and Joseph Edwards Jr., all of Mulberry; daughters, Deborah Asbell, Eagle Lake, Sharon Lacy, Bartow, Marlene Harrington, Mulberry; brother, Joseph Warder, Winter Haven; sisters, Geneva Richardson, Hot Springs, Ark., Marie Adams, Wahneta; 19 grandchildren; and two great-grandchildren.

Services will be at 10 a.m. todayat Bethleham Memorial Cemetery, Mulberry.

Memorial contributions may be made to Good Shepherd Hospice, P.O. Box 7129, Winter Haven, FL 33338.

Whidden-McLean Funeral Home, Bartow.
